Thus to wit have the old poets of the Greeks sung 3 though it is all too widely at variance with true reason. Fire may gain the mastery when more bodies of matter than usual have gathered themselves up out of the infinite 3 and then its powers decay, vanquished in some way or other, or else things perish burnt up by the torrid air.
